1. In the terminal,  run the command: code ~/.bashrc
2. Then Itâ€™ll open a .bashrc  file in the terminal.
3. Add the code below to the bottom of the file.
```
#Removing unnecessary packages, Update the package list, Upgrade all the installed packages
alias updateall='sudo apt-get autoremove -y && sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade -y'

# Alias "bin/magento" to "m" for a one letter shortcut
alias m=bin/magento

# Basic cleanup code for Magento 2 - rm -rf generate
alias mageclean='rm -rf generated/code/* var/cache/* var/di/* var/page_cache/*'

# Full cleanup including view_preprocessed in Magento2
alias magecleanall='rm -rf generated/code/* var/cache/* var/di/* var/page_cache/* var/view_preprocessed/*'

# Install any .deb package easily
alias install-deb='sudo dpkg -i'

#Count the number of commits in a git repository
# Usage: git_commit_count
# Example: git_commit_count
# Output: 42 (number of commits in the current branch)
# This alias counts the number of commits in the current git repository.
# It uses `git rev-list --count HEAD` to get the total number of commits.
# It can be useful for quickly checking the commit history without needing to run a full log command
alias git_commit_count='git rev-list --count HEAD'


# ==============================================================
# To see the full list of available 2.4.x versions:
# ==============================================================
# Usage: mageversions
# Example: mageversions
# Output: 2.4.0, 2.4.1, 2.4.2, etc.
# This alias uses Composer to show the available versions of the Magento product community edition for version 2.4.x.
alias mageversions="composer show magento/product-community-edition 2.4.* --available | grep -m 1 versions"


# n98-magerun2.phar dev tool
alias n98mage='/usr/local/bin/n98-magerun2.phar'

```
4. Run this command: source ~/.bashrc 